## Public Constructors

### iterator() {#ad5a5afe5a3b85db1f4a1d6b656a44a4a}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>llvm::sandboxir::SeedContainer::iterator::iterator (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mapvector">BundleMapT</a> &amp; Map, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mapvector/#a085f340f16ff796202863961ff734902">BundleMapT::iterator</a> MapIt, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">ValT</a> &#42; Vec, int VecIdx)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Iterates over the <code>Map</code> of <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sandboxir/seedbundle">SeedBundle</a> Vectors, starting at <code>MapIt</code>, and <code>Vec</code> at <code>VecIdx</code>, skipping vectors that are completely used.

Iteration order over the keys &#123;Pointer, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sandboxir/type">Type</a>, Opcode&#125; follows <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/densemap">DenseMap</a> iteration order. For a given key, the vectors of SeedBundles will be returned in insertion order. As in the pseudo code below:

for Key,<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sandboxir/value">Value</a> in Bundles for SeedBundleVector in <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sandboxir/value">Value</a> for <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sandboxir/seedbundle">SeedBundle</a> in SeedBundleVector if !SeedBundle.allUsed() ...

Note that the bundles themselves may have additional ordering, created by the subclasses by insertAt. The bundles themselves may also have used instructions.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/transforms/include/llvm/transforms/vectorize/include/llvm/transforms/vectorize/sandboxvectorizer/seedcollector-h/#l00230">230</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/transforms/include/llvm/transforms/vectorize/include/llvm/transforms/vectorize/sandboxvectorizer/seedcollector-h">SeedCollector.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

</SectionDefinition>
